On Tuesday it was reported fire fighters were battling 26 separate fires in the Knysna area.Klatzow said an investigation was needed whenever there were multiple fires simultaneously.But when asked for comment about the cause of the fires James-Brent Styan spokesman for the MEC of Local Government Environmental Affairs and Development Planning said it is unlikely that they will ever know the cause of the fires.More than 10 000 people have now been evacuated from various Knysna suburbs and 150 homes destroyed by flames fanned by heavy winds. It is unusual for fires to start simultaneously said Klatzow one of the leading fire investigators in the country.Read full story: http://www.dispatchlive.co.za/news/2017/06/08/knysna-fires-result-arson/&nbsp;